abstract: Israel announced on Sunday that it will allow Christians in the Gaza Strip to travel to Jerusalem and the West Bank for Christmas.
snippet: Israel announced on Sunday that it will allow Christians in the Gaza Strip to travel to Jerusalem and the West Bank for Christmas.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Israel announced on Sunday that it will allow Christians in the Gaza Strip to travel to Jerusalem and the West Bank for Christmas.
headline_main: Israel to Grant Holiday Travel Permits to Gaza Christians
headline_print_headline: Israel to Grant Holiday Travel Permits to Gaza Christians

abstract: A dispute over a child's haircut ended with gunfire Saturday at a Texas barbershop, according to authorities.
snippet: A dispute over a child's haircut ended with gunfire Saturday at a Texas barbershop, according to authorities.
lead_paragraph: KATY, Texas — A dispute over a child's haircut ended with gunfire Saturday at a Texas barbershop, according to authorities.
headline_main: Police: Texas Barbershop Worker Shot Over Child's Haircut
headline_print_headline: Police: Texas Barbershop Worker Shot Over Child's Haircut

abstract: Aaron Carver scored a career-high 16 points on 7-of-8 shooting from the floor and grabbed 16 rebounds as Old Dominion snapped its eight-game losing streak, rolling past Maryland-Eastern Shore 76-52 on Sunday.
snippet: Aaron Carver scored a career-high 16 points on 7-of-8 shooting from the floor and grabbed 16 rebounds as Old Dominion snapped its eight-game losing streak, rolling past Maryland-Eastern Shore 76-52 on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: NORFOLK, Va. — Aaron Carver scored a career-high 16 points on 7-of-8 shooting from the floor and grabbed 16 rebounds as Old Dominion snapped its eight-game losing streak, rolling past Maryland-Eastern Shore 76-52 on Sunday.
headline_main: Carver Helps Old Dominion Snap Eight-Game Skid
headline_print_headline: Carver Helps Old Dominion Snap Eight-Game Skid

abstract: Over more than 40 years, Ms. Lindsey turned out hot-blooded historical romances set around the world.
snippet: Over more than 40 years, Ms. Lindsey turned out hot-blooded historical romances set around the world.
lead_paragraph: Johanna Lindsey, whose best-selling romance novels told stories of unbridled passion, revenge, submission and abductions among aristocrats, debutantes, pirates and fearless heroines, died on Oct. 27 in Nashua, N.H. She was 67.
